race.comment: Sparingly raced five-year-old VERBIL (2) took a while to hit top gear and just missed last start over 1250m at Newcastle. Fitter for two runs back from a spell, gets the blinkers on for the first time, and McDonald takes over. Plenty to like about his chances. BELIEVE IN ANGELS (7) hasn't been far away in his two runs this prep, the latest a one-length defeat over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Needs this trip now and should be right there at the finish. RINGAROSA (6) opened this prep with four solid efforts in town then appreciated the drop in grade when successful over 1300m at Bathurst most recently. Honest mare who will give a good account again. STAGNUM (5) is back from a three-month spell. Wasn't beaten far in two runs last prep, both in Saturday grade. Big chance in this company. SHOW COUNTY (4) can be a bit hard to follow. One for the exotics only.
